HEADWORD: Appian
<hw>Ap"pi*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Appius</ets>, <ets>Appianus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
Appius.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Appian Way</b></col>, <cd>the great paved highway from
ancient Rome trough Capua to Brundisium, now Brindisi, constructed
partly by <etsep>Appius</etsep> Claudius, about 312 <sc>b.
c.</sc></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Applaud</ent>⟦br⟧
